Package: regplane3D
Type: Package
Title: Plotting regression predictions in 3D
Version: 0.1.0
Author: c(
  person("Denis", "Cohen", email = "denis.cohen@mzes.uni-mannheim.de <denis.cohen@mzes.uni-mannheim.de", role = c("cre","aut")),
  person("Nick", "Baumann", email = "nbaumann@mail.uni-mannheim.de", role = c("com", "ctb")))
Description: \code{regplane3D}is a convenience tool for plotting regression predictions in 3D, based on the \code{\link{plot3D}} packge. It plots grid of conditional expectations in three dimensional space, optionally with their respective confidence intervals (\code{regplane3D}, \code{twoplanes3D}). User can optionally add a threedimensional histogram at the bottom of the plot.
